        "Love & Relationships": "<div>In love, the Rabbit is tender, romantic, and devoted. They view relationships as a sanctuary and seek a partner who can provide security and emotional support. They are not interested in volatile or unpredictable romances.<br/><br/><strong>Relationship Dynamics:</strong> Rabbits show love through thoughtful gestures and creating a comfortable home life. They need reassurance and gentleness. Harshness or constant arguing will cause them to withdraw into their shell. Once they trust a partner, they are incredibly loyal and nurturing.<br/><br/><strong>Challenges:</strong> Their fear of conflict can lead to passive-aggressive behavior. Instead of addressing issues directly, a Rabbit might become silent or distant. They need to learn that healthy disagreement is a part of intimacy, not a threat to it.</div>",
        "Zodiac Compatibility": "<div>Rabbits need partners who appreciate their gentle nature and won't overwhelm them.<br/><br/><strong>Best Matches:</strong> <br/>- <strong>Goat:</strong> Share a love for art and peace; a very harmonious union.<br/>- <strong>Dog:</strong> The Dog's loyalty provides the security the Rabbit craves.<br/>- <strong>Pig:</strong> Both are domestic and love the good life; they enjoy caring for each other.<br/><br/><strong>Challenging Matches:</strong> <br/>- <strong>Rooster:</strong> The Rooster's blunt perfectionism hurts the sensitive Rabbit.<br/>- <strong>Rat:</strong> Their values and personalities often clash, leading to misunderstandings.</div>",
        "Family and Social Life": "<div>Family is the center of a Rabbit's world. They are often the glue that holds the family together, organizing gatherings and ensuring everyone gets along. As parents, they are gentle and protective, ensuring their children have a well-rounded and cultured upbringing.<br/><br/><strong>Socially:</strong> Rabbits are wonderful hosts. They prefer intimate dinner parties with close friends over loud, crowded clubs. They are known for their impeccable manners and their ability to make everyone feel at ease. They choose their friends carefully, valuing quality over quantity.</div>",
        "Education & Learning Style": "<div>Rabbits are observant and quiet learners. They prefer a structured and peaceful learning environment. They are not the type to raise their hand constantly, but they absorb everything. <br/><br/><strong>Preferred Subjects:</strong> They gravitate towards the humanities—literature, history, and art. Psychology and sociology also interest them as they enjoy understanding human nature. They have a good memory and an eye for detail, which helps them in academic pursuits.</div>",
        "Health Tendencies": "<div>Rabbits tend to have a delicate constitution. Their health is closely linked to their emotional state; stress often manifests physically as digestive issues or insomnia.<br/><br/><strong>Watch Out For:</strong> Anxiety is a common issue. They need to be careful about not internalizing stress. They should also watch their diet, as they can have sensitive stomachs.<br/><br/><strong>Wellness Advice:</strong> A peaceful routine is essential. Gentle exercise like yoga or tai chi is perfect. Spending time in nature or engaging in artistic hobbies helps them recharge and maintain emotional balance.</div>",
        "Wealth & Money Mindset": "<div>Rabbits are generally lucky with money, but they are also very cautious. They are not gamblers. They prefer steady accumulation of wealth over get-rich-quick schemes. <br/><br/><strong>Financial Style:</strong> They are astute managers of their finances. They rarely spend beyond their means and always have a rainy-day fund. They enjoy spending on high-quality items for their home or wardrobe but look for value.<br/><br/><strong>Advice:</strong> While their caution is an asset, it can also make them miss out on good investment opportunities. Learning to take calculated risks can help them grow their wealth significantly.</div>",
        "Years & Associated Elements": "<div>The element of the birth year shapes the Rabbit's personality:<br/><br/><ul class=\"list_style\">\n<li><strong>Wood Rabbit (1975, 2035):</strong> Generous and easygoing. More adaptable and open to change than other Rabbits.</li>\n<li><strong>Fire Rabbit (1927, 1987):</strong> Charismatic and active. Has more leadership qualities and hides their emotions less.</li>\n<li><strong>Earth Rabbit (1939, 1999):</strong> Practical and grounded. Very hardworking and focused on building material security.</li>\n<li><strong>Metal Rabbit (1951, 2011):</strong> Resilient and ambitious. Has a stronger will and can be more emotionally guarded.</li>\n<li><strong>Water Rabbit (1963, 2023):</strong> Gentle and intuitive. Very sensitive to others' vibrations and extremely supportive.</li>\n</ul></div>",
        "Famous People Born": "<div>The Rabbit sign has graced the world with many talented and elegant figures.<br/><br/><ul class=\"list_style\">\n<li><strong>Albert Einstein</strong> (1879)</li>\n<li><strong>Angelina Jolie</strong> (1975)</li>\n<li><strong>Brad Pitt</strong> (1963)</li>\n<li><strong>Michael Jordan</strong> (1963)</li>\n<li><strong>Whitney Houston</strong> (1963)</li>\n<li><strong>David Beckham</strong> (1975)</li>\n<li><strong>Lionel Messi</strong> (1987)</li>\n<li><strong>Johnny Depp</strong> (1963)</li>\n<li><strong>Kate Winslet</strong> (1975)</li>\n</ul></div>"
