        "Career & Work Life": "<div>Dragons are built for success. They are innovators and pioneers who thrive in leadership roles. A routine job will suffocate their spirit. They need challenges, risks, and the freedom to implement their grand ideas.<br/><br/><strong>Ideal Paths:</strong> They excel as CEOs, politicians, and entrepreneurs. Their creative flair also makes them great architects, designers, or film directors. Any role that allows them to leave a legacy appeals to them. They are natural trailblazers who are not afraid to go where no one has gone before.<br/><br/><strong>Growth Areas:</strong> Dragons need to learn the art of delegation. They often try to do everything themselves because they think no one else can do it better. Learning to trust a team and accept feedback is crucial for their long-term growth.</div>",
        "Love & Relationships": "<div>In love, Dragons are passionate and protective lovers. They are often surrounded by admirers but can be selective about who they let into their inner circle. They look for a partner who is their equal—someone strong enough to stand beside them, not behind them.<br/><br/><strong>Relationship Dynamics:</strong> They are generous and devoted partners who will shower their loved ones with attention. However, they also need their independence. A clingy partner will quickly drive a Dragon away. They respect strength and intelligence and want a relationship that is as exciting as their life.<br/><br/><strong>Challenges:</strong> Their ego can be a hurdle. Dragons hate to admit they are wrong. They need to learn humility and compromise to keep harmony in a relationship.</div>",
        "Zodiac Compatibility": "<div>The Dragon pairs best with signs that can match their intensity or offer unwavering support.<br/><br/><strong>Best Matches:</strong> <br/>- <strong>Rat:</strong> The resourceful Rat complements the Dragon’s power perfectly.<br/>- <strong>Monkey:</strong> Shares the Dragon’s love for innovation and fun; an unstoppable duo.<br/>- <strong>Rooster:</strong> The practical Rooster provides the grounding structure the Dragon needs.<br/><br/><strong>Challenging Matches:</strong> <br/>- <strong>Dog:</strong> The Dog’s pessimism clashes with the Dragon’s optimism.<br/>- <strong>Ox:</strong> Both are too stubborn to get along smoothly.</div>",
        "Family and Social Life": "<div>Family is a source of pride for the Dragon. They are often the 'star' of the family or the one everyone looks up to. They take their responsibilities seriously and will go to great lengths to help family members succeed.<br/><br/><strong>Socially:</strong> Dragons are popular and often the center of attention at gatherings. They have a wide circle of acquaintances but a smaller group of trusted friends. They are loyal to their friends but expect loyalty in return. If betrayed, they do not forgive easily.</div>",
        "Education & Learning Style": "<div>Dragons are quick learners who are driven by purpose. They aren't interested in learning for the sake of it; they want to know how they can use that knowledge to achieve something. <br/><br/><strong>Preferred Subjects:</strong> They gravitate towards subjects that offer power or influence—law, business, political science, and philosophy. They also have a creative side that draws them to the arts. They enjoy debate and intellectual challenges.</div>",
        "Health Tendencies": "<div>Dragons are blessed with a strong constitution and high energy levels. However, they push themselves harder than any other sign, often neglecting their physical needs in pursuit of their goals.<br/><br/><strong>Watch Out For:</strong> Burnout is their biggest risk. Stress-related issues like tension headaches or high blood pressure can occur. They may also neglect regular meals or sleep when focused on a project.<br/><br/><strong>Wellness Advice:</strong> Incorporating relaxation into their routine is vital. Yoga, meditation, or spending time in nature can help balance their fiery energy. They need to learn that rest is not time wasted, but fuel for their next conquest.</div>",
        "Wealth & Money Mindset": "<div>Money flows easily to the Dragon. They have a knack for spotting opportunities and the courage to seize them. They view money as a tool to achieve their dreams and enjoy life.<br/><br/><strong>Financial Style:</strong> They are generous spenders but also savvy earners. They aren't afraid of high-risk investments if the potential accumulation is high. They often attain wealth later in life after calming their impulsive nature.<br/><br/><strong>Advice:</strong> While they are good at making money, keeping it can be a challenge due to their lavish tastes. Hiring a good financial advisor can help them build lasting wealth.</div>",
        "Years & Associated Elements": "<div>The element adds a specific flavor to the Dragon's power:<br/><br/><ul class=\"list_style\">\n<li><strong>Wood Dragon (1964, 2024):</strong> Creative and open-minded. Less dominating than other Dragons, more willing to collaborate.</li>\n<li><strong>Fire Dragon (1916, 1976):</strong> Ambitious and explosive. A natural leader who commands attention but needs to control their temper.</li>\n<li><strong>Earth Dragon (1928, 1988):</strong> Grounded and logical. More level-headed and focuses on building a solid foundation.</li>\n<li><strong>Metal Dragon (1940, 2000):</strong> Unyielding and focused. Has immense willpower and integrity but can be inflexible.</li>\n<li><strong>Water Dragon (1952, 2012):</strong> Observant and adaptable. Uses wisdom rather than force to get their way.</li>\n</ul></div>",
        "Famous People Born": "<div>The Dragon roster is full of influential icons who have shaped history and culture.<br/><br/><ul class=\"list_style\">\n<li><strong>Bruce Lee</strong> (1940)</li>\n<li><strong>Rihanna</strong> (1988)</li>\n<li><strong>John Lennon</strong> (1940)</li>\n<li><strong>Sandra Bullock</strong> (1964)</li>\n<li><strong>Keanu Reeves</strong> (1964)</li>\n<li><strong>Adele</strong> (1988)</li>\n<li><strong>Shakira</strong> (1977)</li>\n<li><strong>Vladimir Putin</strong> (1952)</li>\n<li><strong>Martin Luther King III</strong> (1957)</li>\n<li><strong>Reese Witherspoon</strong> (1976)</li>\n</ul></div>"
