        "Career & Work Life": "<div>Snakes excel in careers that require intellect, analysis, and problem-solving. They hate noise and stress, preferring to work in quiet environments where they can focus. They are not fond of routine tasks and need work that engages their mind.<br/><br/><strong>Ideal Paths:</strong> They make excellent scientists, analysts, and researchers. Their refined taste also suits them for careers in the arts, fashion, or interior design. Many Snakes are successful entrepreneurs or financiers because of their shrewd judgment and patience.<br/><br/><strong>Growth Areas:</strong> Snakes can sometimes be too cautious or slow to act. They need to learn that sometimes taking a calculated risk is necessary for growth. Also, learning to collaborate openly without suspicion will help them in team environments.</div>",
        "Love & Relationships": "<div>In love, the Snake is seductive and intense. They choose their partners carefully. They are not interested in frivolous flings; they want a deep, soul-mate connection. Once they fall in love, they are possessive and protective.<br/><br/><strong>Relationship Dynamics:</strong> Snakes are sensual and romantic partners who know how to make their loved ones feel special. However, they demand total loyalty. Betrayal is the ultimate sin for a Snake, and they rarely forgive it. They need a partner who can handle their intensity and provide them with security.<br/><br/><strong>Challenges:</strong> Jealousy is the Snake's biggest hurdle. They can become suffocating if they feel insecure. Learning to trust their partner and giving them space is essential for a healthy relationship.</div>",
        "Zodiac Compatibility": "<div>Snakes need partners who are reliable and can understand their complex nature.<br/><br/><strong>Best Matches:</strong> <br/>- <strong>Rooster:</strong> Only the Rooster can truly appreciate the Snake’s wisdom; they are intellectual soulmates.<br/>- <strong>Ox:</strong> The Ox provides the stability the Snake needs and happily lets the Snake take the lead creatively.<br/><br/><strong>Challenging Matches:</strong> <br/>- <strong>Tiger:</strong> The Tiger’s impulsiveness clashes with the Snake’s deliberate nature.<br/>- <strong>Pig:</strong> The Pig is too naive for the sophisticated Snake; they often misunderstand each other.</div>",
        "Family and Social Life": "<div>Snakes keep a small circle. They are private people who cherish their home as a sanctuary. Family is important, but they often maintain a certain independence even within the family unit. They are the wise aunt or uncle whom everyone goes to for secrets.<br/><br/><strong>Socially:</strong> They are selective socializers. They prefer intimate dinner parties to loud crowds. They are excellent conversationalists, often holding court with fascinating stories or insights. They don't need to be the center of attention, but their presence is always felt.</div>",
        "Education & Learning Style": "<div>Snakes are deep learners. They don't just skim the surface; they want to understand the 'why' and 'how'. They are often self-taught experts in niche subjects. <br/><br/><strong>Preferred Subjects:</strong> Psychology, philosophy, and occult sciences fascinate them. They also excel in biology or chemistry—anything that requires uncovering hidden truths. They are patient students who are willing to put in the time to master a subject completely.</div>",
        "Health Tendencies": "<div>Snakes generally have good health, but their constitution is tied to the seasons. They prefer warmth and dislike cold. They are prone to stress-related illnesses because they internalize their emotions.<br/><br/><strong>Watch Out For:</strong> Digestive issues and heart health should be monitored. Insomnia can also be a problem when their mind won't shut off.<br/><br/><strong>Wellness Advice:</strong> Snakes need plenty of relaxation. Warm baths, spa days, and peaceful vacations are essential for their well-being. They should also pay attention to their diet, eating fresh, warm foods to maintain their energy.</div>",
        "Wealth & Money Mindset": "<div>Snakes are often financially successful. They have a talent for spotting lucrative opportunities that others miss. They are notoriously frugal with others but will spend lavishly on themselves.<br/><br/><strong>Financial Style:</strong> They are strategic investors. They don't gamble; they calculate. They prefer to have a substantial safety net and rarely find themselves in debt. They view money as a means to maintain their independence and lifestyle.<br/><br/><strong>Advice:</strong> Snakes should be careful not to become miserly. While saving is good, generosity can open doors that hoarding cannot. They should also avoid letting their suspicious nature stop them from taking good advice.</div>",
        "Years & Associated Elements": "<div>The element determines the Snake's shade of wisdom:<br/><br/><ul class=\"list_style\">\n<li><strong>Wood Snake (1965, 2025):</strong> Kind and imaginative. More social and grounded than other Snakes.</li>\n<li><strong>Fire Snake (1917, 1977):</strong> Charismatic and active. Has a magnetic personality and loves the spotlight more than others.</li>\n<li><strong>Earth Snake (1929, 1989):</strong> Warm and relaxed. Reliable and less secretive, focusing on slow, steady progress.</li>\n<li><strong>Metal Snake (1941, 2001):</strong> Willful and calculating. Extremely focused on success and can be ruthless if crossed.</li>\n<li><strong>Water Snake (1953, 2013):</strong> Insightful and influential. Highly intuitive and manipulative, often getting their way without anyone noticing.</li>\n</ul></div>",
        "Famous People Born": "<div>The Snake sign is home to many thinkers, artists, and influential leaders.<br/><br/><ul class=\"list_style\">\n<li><strong>Taylor Swift</strong> (1989)</li>\n<li><strong>Oprah Winfrey</strong> (1954)</li>\n<li><strong>J.K. Rowling</strong> (1965)</li>\n<li><strong>Daniel Radcliffe</strong> (1989)</li>\n<li><strong>Bob Dylan</strong> (1941)</li>\n<li><strong>Audrey Hepburn</strong> (1929)</li>\n<li><strong>Pablo Picasso</strong> (1881)</li>\n<li><strong>Abraham Lincoln</strong> (1809)</li>\n<li><strong>Kanye West</strong> (1977)</li>\n<li><strong>Tom Hardy</strong> (1977)</li>\n</ul></div>"
