        "Career & Work Life": "<div>Horses thrive in active, fast-paced careers. They cannot sit still in a cubicle all day. They need variety, interaction, and the freedom to make their own decisions. Routine is their enemy.<br/><br/><strong>Ideal Paths:</strong> Sales, journalism, and public relations are perfect fits because they allow for travel and meeting new people. They also excel as performers, translators, or tour guides. Their ability to think quickly makes them great at crisis management or emergency services.<br/><br/><strong>Growth Areas:</strong> The biggest challenge for a Horse is following through. They are great at starting projects but terrible at finishing them. Learning discipline and attention to detail helps them turn their flashes of brilliance into sustained success.</div>",
        "Love & Relationships": "<div>In love, Horses are romantic and passionate, falling in love easily and intensely. They wear their hearts on their sleeves. However, their need for independence can cause conflict; they want intimacy but feat entrapment.<br/><br/><strong>Relationship Dynamics:</strong> They are fun and exciting partners who will whisk their loved ones away on spontaneous adventures. But they can also be flighty. If a relationship becomes too routine or demanding, they might look for the exit. They need a partner who understands their need for space and doesn't try to control them.<br/><br/><strong>Challenges:</strong> Horses need to learn that commitment isn't a cage. Developing emotional maturity and sticking around when things get tough are lessons they often learn later in life.</div>",
        "Zodiac Compatibility": "<div>Horses need partners who can keep up with them and offer them freedom.<br/><br/><strong>Best Matches:</strong> <br/>- <strong>Tiger:</strong> Shares the Horse’s love for adventure and freedom; a thrilling couple.<br/>- <strong>Goat:</strong> The gentle Goat relies on the Horse, which makes the Horse feel needed and grounded.<br/>- <strong>Dog:</strong> The loyal Dog provides a stable home base for the wandering Horse.<br/><br/><strong>Challenging Matches:</strong> <br/>- <strong>Rat:</strong> The Rat’s need for security clashes with the Horse’s need for risk.<br/>- <strong>Ox:</strong> The Ox is too slow and steady for the galloping Horse.</div>",
        "Family and Social Life": "<div>Horses often leave home early to explore the world. They love their family but prefer to love them from a distance where they can maintain their independence. They are the exciting relative who visits with gifts and stories from abroad.<br/><br/><strong>Socially:</strong> They are popular and have a wide network of acquaintances. They love parties, events, and gatherings. However, they can be unreliable friends, sometimes canceling plans at the last minute if something more exciting comes up. Their true friends know not to take this personally.</div>",
